rComments: The lecture material itself is very difficult but JB is a brilliant prof that makes everything crystal clear in his lectures. So my advice is never skip his class. He is very helpful if you go to his office hours, or just drop by his office and ask questions. Would love to have him again but he got promoted to Dalhousie.

Pretty good professor, but the workload is deceptively high in this course. And his class touches on material from several assigned books which makes it difficult to track down the correct information.
By far one of the best professors I've had.
